******
[3] Georgia
Date: Mon 19 Jul 2010
Source: The Examiner, Associated Press (AP) report, information from
WALB-TV [edited]
<http://www.washingtonexaminer.com/breaking/whooping-cough-cases-confirmed-in-ga-98794624.html>


Some Georgia health officials are warning parents to vaccinate
children after cases of whooping cough have increased in Georgia.

Authorities tell WALB that 46 cases of the transmissible disease,
also called pertussis, have been confirmed in Georgia.

Health officials are looking into cases of other possible cases in
Tift, Turner, and Grady counties.

